On the special directive of Inspector General, NH&MP, Motorway Police South Zone has arranged special awareness camp at Ravi Toll Plaza, Motorway M-2.
SSP Masroor Alam Kolachi personally supervised the camp during which special gifts and road safety pamphlets and brochures printed were distributed among the commuters and motorists at all Ravi Toll Plaza, Lahore.
The Flowers and gift hampers were distributed with the aim to share the happiness of Eid and strengthen public and police relationship. The road users are requested to contacted Motorway Police personnel or NH&MP Helpline (130) for any complaint in this regard.

Just happened; we were coming back from Police Lines after attending a Janaza and we stopped on a red signal behind many cars. I usually travel in a car with no blue light and even my security car does not use siren or blue light. Sudden, sitting in the back seat I noticed that a car with family could not restart on green signal, an officer, I yet don't know what's his name, rushed in and single handed pushed from behind for the car to start. It just started off and vanished into rush of cars. The traffic continued as if nothing had happened. He might not even know that I captured the moment myself in heavy rush; I salute you my dear: you have made me proud.

Source : IGP Islamabad Tariq Masood Yasin.

PageName: National Highways & Motorway Police Pakistan - Official
Post:
NH&MP took stern action against the complaints of overcharging by the transporters during Eid-ul-Azha

Upon the directions of Inspector General Shaukat Hayat, officers of NH&MP took stern action against the complaints of overcharging by the transporters during Eid-ul-Azha and returned 06 million rupees to passengers in total.  

As per details NH&MP officers took prompt action in Islamabad, Rawalpindi, Attock, Jehulm, Gujranwala, Gujrat, Lahore, Sargodha, Faisalabad, Sheikhupura, Chakwal, Multan, Okara, Khanewal, Bahawalpur, Rahim Yar Khan, Sukkur, Moro, Hyderabad, Karachi and many other districts against the complaints of overcharging by the transporters and retrieved thousands of rupees and returned to the passengers. 

On 12-09-2016 on motorways the total amount 11,3970/- rupees and on highways total amount 59,34100/- rupees have been retrieved and returned to the passengers. Timely and quick action of Motorway Police was highly appreciated. Uptill now the total amount returned to the  passengers on motorways and highways is 1,9885950/- rupees.

PageName: National Highways & Motorway Police Pakistan - Official
Post:
Two culprits wanted in 160 criminal cases are arrested on Motorway 
In Khankadogran sector M-2 South Motorway zone on 95 south bound a mini truck was noted by DSP Naeem through main Islamabad control. The mini truck was roundup by officers of T-3, operational officer and arrested 02 culprits. According to DSP the both culprits are wanted in 160 criminal cases in Islamabad. The culprits alongwith truck were handed over to local Police Station Koral Islamabad for further action.

PageName: National Highways & Motorway Police Pakistan - Official
Post:
Important:
"An incident of an attempt of robbery by pelting stone on window of car at 10:30 pm on the intervening night of 8/9 September 2016 was highlighted by a complainant Omar Shahzad on social media....
On the directions of DIG Motorways Imtiaz Shah, the matter was immediately inquired by the concerned SSP/Sector commander Masroor Alam Kolachi along with DPO Sargodha. They visited the spot, inquired the matter and fixed responsibility on officer of NH&MP who did not follow SOP properly and did not respond to commuter positively.  Delinquent officer SI/PO M.Iqbal has been suspended  and departmental proceedings have been initiated against him.
Moreover upon directions of DIG Motorways, patrolling has been intensified in sensitive areas of adjoining beats through special crime squads. District police has also been coordinated in this regard. DPO Sargodha has beefed up security in these areas through special patrolling of Elite and Police Station mobile."

Post:
NOWSHERA: Four Motorway police officials were allegedly physically abused by Army Personnel who was travelling in two vehicles on the Grand Trunk Road, an official reported on Saturday.

Deputy Superintendent Jan Bahadur of NHMP told reporters that Motorway Police officials signalled two over speeding cars to stop near Jehangira, but they didnâ€™t stop.

After the vehicles were chased and caught, those who seated in the vehicles introduced themselves as security forces. The event took place near Khairabad.

Deputy Superintendent said that those travelling in the two vehicles were in civil clothes and they immediately started making calls for assistance.

More security forces personnel arrived on scene in four vehicles and roughed up the Motorway Police officials.

security forces personnel were accompanied by two army majors, who along with the other men severely beat up the officials of the Motorway Police and forcibly took them to the Attock Fort along with their vehicle.

Bahadur complained that the officials of the Motorway Police were kept in illegal detention by the security forces and were released after high-ups held negotiations to secure their release.

The four injured officials of the Motorway Police, including Inspector Mohsin Toru, Head Constables Jalal Shah and Atif Khattak and driver Shah Zeb, were taken to the District Headquarters Hospital in Nowshera.

Atif Khattak, who was injured due to the thrashing by the soldiers, said that Captain Daniyal and Captain Qasim, who were in civvies, were involved in reckless driving and were, therefore, signaled to stop due to violation of traffic rules.

He added that the two army officers rang up their colleagues and sought their help and soon a number of soldiers in four vehicles reached the spot and started beating him and his NHMP colleagues.

When contacted, Colonel Shahid of the Pakistan Army told this scribe that an inquiry had been launched into the matter. He said those found guilty would be punished as per the law.

We are to protect & Serve, Capital City Police Lahore

In order to realize the vision of developing safe cities in the province, PPIC3 Centre has been developed for Punjab Police in the city of Lahore, which will be subsequently established in the larger cities of the province.

The PPIC3 Programme also aims to increase public satisfaction levels as real time comparison of suspected persons with criminal and other allied departmental databases will make apprehension of record holders instantaneous.

A major benefit of the project will be traffic management, where public will be informed of traffic density and alternate routes will be planned for them through the Variable Messaging System, and through broadcast; thus minimizing journey times and stops at traffic signals, which will save enormous costs of fuel and time. E-Challans will be also possible through the system.

Making changes to the Punjab Police culture, structure, technology and processes will enable provision of integrated emergency services like Rescue 1122, Fire Fighting and disaster relief to the police and public.

Anticipatory technologies will ensure that police responders are available for real time monitoring of processions and law and order situations. It will ensure efficient resource deployment for optimum effect.

Enhanced monitoring of the public spaces, better utilization of police resources and improved command and control infrastructure will lead to better security for the capital city and its residents and visitors.
Enhanced monitoring of the public places, under the project in Lahore, 10000 latest CCTV cameras have been installed.

The Programme envisages that roughly 20 percent of crimes such as rioting, destruction of public and private property, 28-30 percent of vehicular crime, and 15-20 percent reduction in crimes against property such as house burglary, robbery, and street crime will be achieved in the first five years of operation.

Secure Police Communication
The Police will be on a dedicated LTE/4G network for secure communication through UAVs and Mobile command and control centres.

The SSP/Principal Nazeer Ahmed Mirbahar surprisingly visited the law classes. During the visit he observed the standard of teaching, discipline and curriculum in law classes, as he not only interacted with the trainees in order to seek their attention towards the lecture but also himself delivered his skillful lectures about the topics going on in classes. He further visited the model police station where he shared his field experience with the trainees to enhance their capability of preparation of police cases according to the different nature of crime.

The SSP/Principal Police Training College, Shahdadpur conducted a DARBAR of trainees & Staff to know their problems. While addressing to the DARBAR, the Principal expressed his main concern to boast up the training standard up to the mark of modern policing for the safeguard of public. As during the DARBAR, some of the trainees of ASI probationers Course undergoing at this institute apprised the principal of their grievances, the Principal immediately addressed their grievances and also passed an order with regard to resolve their problems, he further said no any stone will be left un-turn to provide every lawful facilities to trainees as well as staff of Police Training College, Shahdadpur.

The SSP/PRINCIPAL Police Training College, Shahdadpur conducted a reformative meeting with the most experienced instructors of P.T.C, Shahdadpur with regard to ensure the completion of law syllabus and physical training events within the stipulated period along with getting the maximum goals  of training.
The PRINCIPAL further interacted with some of the most veteran instructors and ask them to impart your expertise in order to enable the trainees to counter the terrorism in society and also safeguard the public as well.

The SSP/Principal Police Training College, Shahdadpur conducted a comprehensive briefing to the Drill Instructors for imparting modern police field Training to trainees undergoing at this institution. He not only directed to Chief Drill Instructor with regard to bring the modern reformations in training but also ensure the norm of discipline of training rules. Further more the SSP/ Principal NAZIR AHMED MIRBAHAR; PSP shared   his professional expertise with the instructors so that Instructors may train the trainees up the mark of training standard.

A farewell party was held in the honor of Drill Staff of P.T.C, Shahdadpur. The SSP/Principal Hassan Sardar Ahmed Khan was a chief guest of the party as on this occasion, the retired staff presented the traditional cap to him and the principal also honored them by same way. At the end of the party the Principal appreciated their marvelous services to this Institution. All the retired officials heartily thanked the participation of the principal in the farewell party.

Today SSP/Principal Police Training College, Shahdadpur renamed the Lecture Hall of P.T.C Shahdadpur  by the name of great hero â€œSHAHEED MUHAMMAD RAFIQ QURESHIâ€ on this occasion, the Principal expressed his views with regard to the martyrdom that the sacrifice of Shaheed Rafiq Qureshi can never be forgotten to the end of the world and Sindh Police is highly proud of him.

On 19-09-2016, The SSP/ PRINCIPAL Police Training College, Shahdadpur conducted a DARBAR of staff members as well as trainees undergoing various courses to redress their multi issues. In DARBAR HALL so many trainees of different courses and also staff of P.T.C, Shahdadpur apprised the principal of their issues. As in connection with redressing the issues, and grievances of staff members and trainees ,the principal immediately on the spot resolved their some problems and also passed the necessary instructions for others. At the end of the address, the Principal assured to all of them of his every lawful cooperation and affection as well.

The SSP/Principal Hassan Sardar Ahmed Khan paid the great tribute to Shaheed Police Constable Rafiq Qureshi for his gallantry who deliberately risked his own life to save lots of lives of other people at the eid congregation in Khanpur town of Shikarpur. While praising the martyr The Principal burst out with tears. As in conducted DARBAR all the present staff and trainees along with Principal observed lots of prayers for the great hero of Police Department. Furthermore, in memory of the great martyrdom of Police Constable, the Principal Police Training College, Shahdadpur named the lecture hall after the shaheed RAFIQ QURESHI.

The SSP/Principal Police Training College, Shahdadpur Hassan Sardar Ahmed Khan organized the blood donation camp at this institution on 06-09-2016 to save the lives of THALASSEMIA effected Children in association with Thalassemia care center, housing society Nawabshah. The training staff of P.T.C Shahdadpur and as well as the trainees undergoing various courses voluntarily donated their blood with the great passion.
 As in connection with collecting the blood, The Principal not only facilitated the blood collection team but also in his supervision, he got the blood screening test of volunteers conducted in view of disease risk factors. The panel of doctors highly appreciated the paramount cooperation of principal in efforts of saving the lives of   thalassemic patients.

The SSP/Principal police Training college, Shahdadpur paid the great tribute to the martyrs of 6th September 1965 who laid their lives down for the protection of beloved country â€œPAKISTANâ€ further while expressing his views in the honor of great heroes of this event he said â€œOUR HEROES GAVE THEIR TODAY FOR OUR TOMORROWâ€ and also has stoned the lesson of sacrifices for the protection of country to the end of the world.
                            The Principal, on the occasion of this day requested to all â€PAKISTANIESâ€  letâ€™s vow  to progress the  beloved homeland  and also honor its solidarity, integrity, prosperity, peace and will never leave any stone unturned to protect home land â€œPAKISTANâ€ he also prayed to ALMIGHTY ALLAH â€œMAY PAKISTAN PROGRESS BY LEAPS AND BOUNDâ€ 
â€œPAKISTAN ZINDA BADâ€

The SSP/Principal, P.T.C, Shahdadpur Hassan Sardar Ahmed Khan visited the Aazadi Train at the invitation of higher authority of Pakistan railway Shahdadpur on the arrival of  Aazadi Train, which  started its month-long journey from Islamabad Margalla Railways Station on August 11 and arrived @ Shahdadpur Railways Station on 02-09-2016.
The famous personalities of Shahdadpur welcomed the Principal to share such a great historical moment with them. During the visit  SSP/ Principal recorded his golden words in the visit book of train and also appreciated  to train staff. The all railway official and social workers thanked the Principal to reserve his valuable time for this occasion.

Post:
After Biman DC10, PIA 74M is another major flight that I must get on. I am glad that the opportunity came up during my 2 weeks of working in Hong Kong. Here are the flight details.

Ticket HKG-BKK Economy Class one way HK$1290 (inc tax) (US166)

STD 2240 ATD 0045 Delay 2hr 05 mins
STA 0030 ATA 0245 Delay 2hr 15 mins
Seat 83A

At check in I was informed the incoming flight from Islamabad and Bangkok were delayed due to sick patient onboard. Departure gate was 17 and boarding call was made at 2350 hoping for a 0015 departure. After boarding this was further delayed to 0045 without explanation. I compainted to the station manager at check in and he promptly upgrade me to Economy Plus class situated in the upper deck of the B747 classic.
